vegas_pool_halls.name: Griff's Wasteland Cues
vegas_pool_halls.description: Pre-war upscale pool hall, now a scavenger hangout with 30+ salvaged tables. The King was last seen here before his disappearance.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Cue D's Rack & Ruin
vegas_pool_halls.description: 25+ tables still standing. Tournaments every night - winner takes the pot and keeps their kneecaps. The King left a challenge carved into table 7.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Ballz Deep Billiards
vegas_pool_halls.description: Near the ruined Strip, 30 Rasson tables still level after 200 years. The King's final tournament was held here.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Good Timez Tavern
vegas_pool_halls.description: 24-hour pre-war pool hall, now a wastelander refuge. Irradiated Nuka-Cola on tap. The King's favorite late-night spot.

vegas_pool_halls.name: New Vegas Cue Club
vegas_pool_halls.description: 24 tables, 24/7, 200+ years running. Ghouls remember when The King trained champions here.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Backstage Bunker Bar
vegas_pool_halls.description: Fremont Street survivor hideout. The King's legendary cue was displayed in a rad-proof case here.

vegas_pool_halls.name: The Nerd's Nest
vegas_pool_halls.description: Geek refuge with salvaged arcade machines and billiard tables. Pre-war comic books line the walls.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Billiards & Barter
vegas_pool_halls.description: Henderson's last standing pool supply shop. Trade caps for cue chalk and table felt.

vegas_pool_halls.name: On Cue Outpost
vegas_pool_halls.description: North Vegas pool haven turned militia checkpoint. Show your cue skills to pass.

vegas_pool_halls.name: Putter's Ridge Hideaway
vegas_pool_halls.description: Henderson landmark - half bar, half bunker. The King's legendary cue rests in the vault below.
